Durban - The lone gunman who entered courtroom on Monday and fatally wounded two people is believed to be a policeman.      Reports are circulating that the police officer entered Regional Court O and shot a woman believed to be his ex-wife and her brother.     According to Crisis Medical spokesperson, Kyle van Reenen, shortly after midday on Monday, they were alerted to a shooting at the court. "Reports from the scene indicate that a male, approximately 30-years-old allegedly produced a firearm in the courthouse of the ‘O’ Court, shooting a male and female, before turning the gun on himself. The male and female victims were found to have suffered fatal gunshot wounds and were declared deceased on arrival, whilst the man remains in a critical condition," van Reenen said.     The Mercury